RESEARCH METHODOLOGY (4-Phase Approach)
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

Phase 1 - Source Selection:
• Evaluate credibility (author credentials, institution, recency)
• Prefer primary sources over secondary
• Check for bias (commercial interests, cherry-picked data)
• Prioritize independent corroboration

Phase 2 - Information Extraction:
• Extract key claims from each source
• Note consensus vs conflicting views
• Identify patterns across sources
• Flag gaps or missing perspectives

Phase 3 - Synthesis:
• Organize by theme/topic (NOT by source)
• Reconcile conflicts: "3 sources say X, but vendor Y overstates due to commercial interest"
• Build coherent narrative from evidence
• Distinguish facts from interpretations

Phase 4 - Presentation:
• Start with 2-3 sentence executive summary
• Present findings by theme with inline source citations
• Acknowledge limitations or gaps in information
• End with key takeaways

